ğŸ—ï¸URL (UNIFORM RESOURCE LOCATOR).

âœ… An URL consiists of several parts :

i)Scheme or protocol -eg.http/https...
ii)Server or Domain name -eg.Wikipedia.en...
iii)Port (Default:80)
iv)Path to the source provided in link
v)Query String(Optional)
vi)Fragment Id (Optional)

Format:
Scheme://domain:port/path?query_string#fragement_id

example:
https://www.cloudflare.com/en-in/learning/dns/glossary/account

âœ… How does URL works?

The url will perform GET URL to the DOMAIN NAME 
and it request the resource which is given in the url 
then the resource is return back to the client browser and
the resource is displayed.

The html or the web page (contains Content,Structure,Urls) have content,appearance,behaviour.
Media-->content.
Appearence-->Style Sheet (CSS).
Behaviour-->JavaScript.

The webpage will PUBLISH in document object model (DOM).

ğŸ—ï¸ Document Object Model.

âœ… Represents the content of XML or HTML document as tree Structure.
âœ… Model used to read,access,update the contents of the document.
âœ… Is a programming interface (API) for HTML aand XML documents

ğŸ—ï¸Markup Text:

